1. PURPOSE AND SCOPE
We, as DentisToday pay uttermost attention to the protection of personal data, which is a
Constitutional right, of all real persons that we are in contact with during our activities,
including our customers, employees, visitors and business partners and to the compliance of
regulations stated under the Protection of Personal Data Law numbered 6698.
Accordingly, we, in the capacity of the Data Controller, take all kinds of technical and
administrative measures required for the purpose of the prevention of illegal process of personal
data, illegal access to the same and ensuring the retention of the personal data.
We, as DentisToday, aim to inform you with this Protection and Process of Personal Data Policy
on our collection, usage, process, transfer, retention processes and systems of personal data and
our fundamental principles in this regard.

3. PROCEDURES AND PRINCIPLES REGARDING THE PROTECTION OF
PERSONAL DATA
3.1. GENERAL RULES
The protection of personal data has been granted by stating it under Article 20/III of the
Constitution that personal data can be processed only under the circumstances specified under
the law or upon explicit consent of the person. In the direction of such rights granted to personal
data owners, DentisToday processes personal data in accordance with the principles stated
under the relevant legislation or in the circumstances where there is an explicit consent of the
person, as per the following rules:
3.1.1. Processing in Compliance with the Law and Principles of Bona Fides:
DentisToday acts in accordance with all of the legal regulations and the principles of
bonafide in its processing of Personal Data.
3.1.2. Ensuring that Personal Data is Accurate and Up-to-date, when Necessary.
In order for the Personal Data processed by DentisToday to be accurate and up-to-date,
necessary measures are taken and to that the data being processed reflect the real situation,
necessary opportunities are provided to the Data Owners by informing them.
5
3.1.3. Processing for Specific, Explicit and Legitimate Purposes
DentisToday, determines its purpose for processing personal data, which is legitimate and
legal, explicitly and specifically. DentisToday processes the personal data as much as is
necessary for and in connection with the commercial activity it carries out.
3.1.4. Processing for being Relevant with, Limited to and Proportionate to the
Purpose for which it is Processed
DentisToday processes Personal Data in a way that is appropriate for the realization of
the determined purposes and avoids the processing of Personal Data that is not related to
the realization of the purpose or is not needed.
3.1.5. Being Retained for the Period of Time Specified by the Relevant
Legislation or Required for the Purpose for which It is Processed
The personal data processed by DentisToday is retained only for the period of time
specified by the relevant legislation or required for the purpose for which it is processed.
Within this context, DentisToday complies with the period of time, if any, specified for
the retention of personal data under the relevant legislation; if there is no specified period
of time, then it retains such personal data for the period of time required by the purpose
for which it is processed.
3.2. COLLECTION, PROCESSING PERSONAL DATA AND PROCESSING
PURPOSES
Although your personal data processed by DentisToday may vary depending on the health,
physician services, diagnosis and information provided, it is collected through automatic or
non-automatic ways, via call centres, internet sites, online services, online/mobile applications
and similar manners, in writing, orally or electronically. Your personal data of special nature,
particularly your health data and your personal data in general nature and the ones stated below
can be processed by DentisToday being relevant with, limited to and proportionate to the
purposes of health care services given below;
 Your Identity Information: Your name, surname, T.R. Identity number, passport
number or temporary T.C. Identity Number, date of birth, place of birth, marital status,
gender, insurance or patient protocol number, and your other identity data that we can
identify you,
 Your Contact Information: Your address, location, telephone number, electronic mail
address and other contact information, your voice call recordings kept by customer
representatives or patient services in accordance with call centre standards, your
personal data that is obtained when you communicate with us via electronic mail, mail
or other means.
 Your Accounting/Finance Information: Your financial data such as your bank account
number, IBAN number, credit card information, invoicing information.
 Your data regarding private health insurance and data of Social Security Institution for
the purpose of planning health care services,
 Your camera footage is kept for security and supervision purposes in case you visit
hospitals or dental clinics to be offered to you appropriately,
 Your Health Information: All kinds of personal data of yours related to your health and
sexual life obtained while conducting or as a result of the preliminary diagnosis, final
6
diagnosis, medical diagnosis treatment and nursing services including data such as your
laboratory results, test results, physical examination data, appointment information,
roentgen results, radiologic results, check-up results.
 Your health data and other personal data that you have sent to the Application or sent to
the e-mail address aident@hs01.kep.tr or uploaded to the mobile application having the
tradename of DentisToday.
 In case you make a job application to DentisToday, your CV and other personal data
that are provided in this respect and in case you are an employee of DentisToday or its
related employee, your employment contract and all kinds of your personal data with
regard to your work talent.
 Comments and notes are sent by your side while you are using the mobile application
or our website.
 X-ray, radiologic documents and intraoral, dental and other photos and videos and other
data related to these that have been sent by you or upon the approval of the data owner
by you on behalf of her/him in order to get benefit from the services while using the
mobile application or the website.
All kinds of your personal data (including but not limited to the personal data of special nature)
obtained by DentisToday can be processed, generally, to process public health, to conduct
preventive medicine, preliminary and final medical diagnosis, physician referral, medical
diagnosis, treatment and nursing services including artificial intelligence and machine learning
management, and can be also processed for and limited to the following purposes:
 To confirm your identity.
 To protect public health, to conduct preventive medicine, medical diagnosis, treatment
and nursing services, planning and management of health care services and their
financing.
 To share information requested by the Ministry of Health and other public institutions
and organizations as per the related legislation.
 To plan and manage daily operations in hospitals or dental clinics upon your
confirmation.
 To measure, increase and search the satisfaction of patients by the Hospital
Management, Patient Rights, and Patient Experience departments.
 To supply medicines.
 To inform you regarding your appointment in case you get an appointment.
 To direct you to the most appropriate physician for you, in case you request.
 To share your X-ray, radiologic documents and intraoral and extra oral and related
photos and videos that you have sent and other data of yours in connection with these
with the physician.
 To use as analysis for the purpose of improving the application that will be used as
artificial intelligence and services that you have received from our website.
 To plan required analysis in order to offer you the most appropriate service according
to your requests, demands and needs, in case you use our shopping services.
 To fulfil the financing of your health services, your costs of examination, diagnosis and
treatment by the Patient Services, Financial Affairs, Marketing departments, to share
information requested by private insurance companies within the document to which
Social Security Institution you are registered.
 To fulfil legal and regulatory requirements.

 To conduct risk management and quality development activities by Quality, Patient
Experience, Information Security departments.
 To invoice against our services and to confirm your relationship with contracted
institutions by Patient Services, Financial Affairs, Marketing departments.
 To confirm your relationship with institutions contracted DentisToday.
 To use as evidence in disputes to have arisen.
Your Personal Data obtained and process as per the related legislation, can be retained both in

Furthermore, your personal data stated above, can be processed within the framework of the
provisions of Health Care Services Basic Law numbered 3359, Decree numbered 663 on the

Hospitals, Regulation on the Processing of Personal Health Data and Protection of Privacy and

your consent.
3.3. CONDITIONS FOR PROCESSING OF PERSONAL DATA
The processing conditions of personal data have been regulated by the Law and personal data
is processed by DentisToday in accordance with the conditions specified below.
Other than the exceptions stated under the Law, DentisToday process personal data only by
obtaining the explicit consent of personal data owners. Personal data may be processed without
seeking the explicit consent of the data owner only in circumstances where one of the
following conditions is met:
 Data processing is clearly provided for by the laws,
 Data processing is mandatory for the protection of life or physical integrity of the person
or of any other person who is bodily incapable of giving her/his consent due to actual
impossibility or whose consent is not deemed legally valid,
 Processing of personal data belonging to the parties of an agreement is necessary
provided that it is directly related to the conclusion or fulfilment of such agreement,
 Data processing is mandatory for the data controller to be able to perform its legal
obligations,
 The data is made available to the public by the data owner her/himself,
 Data processing is mandatory for the establishment, exercise or protection of any right,
 Data processing is mandatory for the legitimate interests of the data controller, provided
that this processing shall not violate the fundamental rights and freedoms of the data
owner.
8
3.4. PRECAUTIONS REGARDING THE PROTECTION OF PERSONAL DATA
DentisToday takes technical and administrative precautions to provide an adequate level of
security in accordance with Article 12 of the KVKK in order to prevent unlawful processing of
personal data, to prevent unlawful access to personal data and to ensure the retention of personal
data and it makes the necessary audits or has the same made within this context.
Within this scope, the necessary (a) administrative and (b) technical precautions shall be taken
by DentisToday, (c) the auditing system shall be established under the structure of the Company
n the event where the personal data is disclosed in illegal means shall be taken by DentisToday.
DentisToday takes the technical and administrative precautions in order for the processing of
personal data legally, according to the technological possibilities and implementation costs.
A. Technical Precautions Taken to Ensure Legal Processing of Personal Data,
and to Prevent Illegal Access to Personal Data and to Retain Personal Data in
a Secure Environment
 With regard to the protection of personal data, technical precautions shall be
taken as far as the technological possibilities allow and the precautions taken
are updated and renewed periodically,
 A qualified employee is employed for technical matters,
 Auditing is made at regular intervals for the execution of precautions taken,
 Software and hardware ensure the security is established,
 Access authority to personal data processed by DentisToday is classified
under the relevant company employee in line with the intended processing
purpose.
B. Administrative Precautions Taken to Ensure Legal Processing of Personal
Data, and to Prevent Illegal Access to Personal Data and to Retain Personal
Data in a Secure Environment
 DentisToday informs and trains its employees regarding personal data
protection law.
 Contracts concluded by DentisToday with persons to whom personal data is
transferred in accordance with the law; Provisions are added stating that the
persons to whom personal data are transferred will take the necessary security
measures to protect personal data and ensure that these measures are complied
with in their own organizations.
 The processes carried out by DentisToday should be examined in detail, and
the personal data processing activities carried out within the scope of the
process should be determined specifically for each unit. In this context, the
steps to be taken to ensure that the data processing activities carried out comply
9
with the personal data processing conditions stipulated in the Personal Data
Protection Law should be determined.
 DentisToday must determine the practices that need to be fulfilled to ensure
legal compliance requirements according to company structures, and organize
the necessary administrative measures, in-company policies and training to
ensure the control and continuity of these practices.
 In the contracts and documents governing the legal relationship between
DentisToday and employees, records are placed that impose the obligation not
to process, disclose or use personal data, except for DentisToday's instructions
and exceptions imposed by law, and employees' awareness on this issue is
created and inspections are carried out.
 Employees are informed that they cannot disclose the personal data they have
learned to anyone else in violation of the provisions of the Personal Data
Protection Law or use it for purposes other than the purpose of processing, and
that this obligation will continue after they leave office, and the necessary
commitments are taken from them in this regard.
 The authorities of employees who change their duties or leave their jobs in this
area are removed.
 Signed contracts contain data security provisions.
 Necessary security measures are taken regarding entry and exit to physical
environments containing personal data.
 Physical environments containing personal data are secured against external
risks (fire, flood, etc.). The security of environments containing personal data
is ensured. Personal data is reduced as much as possible.
C. Auditing Activities on Precautions Taken for the Protection of Personal Data
 In accordance with Article 12 of the KVK Law, DentisToday carries out or has
it carried out the necessary audits of the technical and administrative measures
taken within the scope of protecting and ensuring the security of personal data.
These audit results are reported to the relevant unit within the scope of
DentisToday's internal operation and necessary activities are carried out to
improve the measures taken.
 In order to increase employees' knowledge and awareness about the Protection
of Personal Data, training is repeated at regular intervals and tests are carried
out in parallel with the training to measure the information. The staff is
informed about the results of the test and any deficiencies are completed in the
next training period.

3.5. CONDITIONS FOR PROCESSING OF PERSONAL DATA OF SPECIAL
NATURE
DentisToday shows special sensitivity in the processing of Special Personal Data, whose
protection is believed to be of more critical importance for the Data Owner in various aspects.
In Article 6 of the Law, certain personal data that pose the risk of causing victimization or
discrimination when processed unlawfully are designated as "special nature". These data; Data
regarding race, ethnic origin, political thought, philosophical belief, religion, sect or other
beliefs, appearance and clothing, association, foundation or union membership, health, sexual
life, criminal conviction and security measures, as well as biometric and genetic data.
Personal Data of Special Nature is processed by DentisToday in accordance with the Law,
provided that adequate measures to be determined by the Board are taken, in the presence of
the following conditions:
 If the Data Owner has explicit consent or
 If the Data Owner does not have explicit consent; a) The relevant person has explicit
consent, b) It is clearly foreseen by law, c) It is necessary for the protection of the life
or physical integrity of the person who is unable to express his consent due to actual
impossibility or whose consent is not given legal validity, d) It is related to the personal
data made public by the relevant person and is in accordance with the will to make it
public, d) It is mandatory for the establishment, use or protection of a right, e) The
protection of public health, the execution of preventive medicine, medical diagnosis,
treatment and care services and the planning, management and financing of health
services by persons under the obligation of confidentiality or authorized institutions and
organizations. f) It is necessary for the fulfillment of legal obligations in the fields of
employment, occupational health and safety, social security, social services and social
assistance, g) Foundations, associations and other non-profit organizations established
for political, philosophical, religious or union purposes. or entities, provided that it is
in accordance with the legislation they are subject to and their purposes, is limited to
their fields of activity and is not disclosed to third parties; It may be processed if it is
directed towards current or former members and members or persons who are in
regular contact with these organizations and entities.
3.6. PRECAUTIONS REGARDING THE PROTECTION OF PERSONAL DATA OF
SPECIAL NATURE
DentisToday, as the data controller, takes the following precautions for the processing of
Personal Data of Special Nature stated under Article 6 of the Law, pursuant to the Decision of
the Board dated 31.01.2018 and numbered 2018/10:
A. A separate, systematic, manageable and sustainable policy has been determined for
the security of personal data of special nature,
11
B. With regard to employees working for the processing of personal data of special
nature,
 Training is provided regularly to employees on the Law and its related
regulations and the security of Personal Data of Special Nature,
 Confidentiality agreements are concluded,
 For users who have authority to access data, the scope and the duration of their
authority are defined clearly,
 Authorization controls are made periodically,
 Authorities of employees whose jobs are changed or who are resigned from
their jobs in this field are removed immediately. Within this context, the
inventory allocated to such employees by the Data Controller is returned to the
Data Controller.
C. If the environment that the Personal Data of Special Nature is processed, retained
and/or accessed is an electronic environment,
 Personal Data is retained by using cryptographic methods,
 Cryptographic keys are kept in secure and different environments,
 Operation records of all movements realized on the Personal Data are logged
securely.
 Security updates for the environments where the Personal Data kept are
monitored constantly, the necessary security test is made regularly on the same
by us or by others appointed by us, and test results are recorded.
 In case Personal Data is accessed via software, the authorization of the user for
such software is made, the necessary security test is made regularly on the same
by us or by others appointed by us, and test results are recorded.
 In case it is required to access Personal Data remotely, at least a two-stage
identity verification system is provided.
D. If the environment that the Personal Data of Special Nature is processed, retained
and/or accessed is a physical environment;
 Adequate security precautions (against electrical leakage, fire, flood, theft, etc.)
according to the nature of the environment where Personal Data of Special
Nature placed are taken,
 Unauthorized entry and exists are prevented by ensuring the physical security
of such environments.
E. In case Personal Data of Special Nature is going to be transferred
 In case the Personal Data needs to be transferred via e-mail, it is transferred in
encrypted form, via a corporate e-mail address or by using a Registered
Electronic Mail (REM) account,
12
 In case it needs to be transferred via environments such as a Memory stick, CD,
DVD, it is encrypted by cryptographic methods and the cryptographic key is
kept in a different environment.
 In case the transferring is carried out between servers in different physical
environments, data transfer is carried out by establishing a VPN between
servers or by the sFTP method.
 In case it needs to be transferred via paper media, necessary precautions are
taken against risks such as theft, loss, or being seen by unauthorized persons,
and the document is sent in a "Confidential" format.
F. In addition to the precautions stated above, technical and administrative precautions
are also taken into account for ensuring the appropriate security level stated under
the Personal Data Security Guidance announced on the website of the Protection of
Personal Data Authority
3.7. PROCESSING OF IMAGE RECORDS
DentisToday uses intraoral photographs, which are the subject of its activity, to provide the
necessary information to direct you to your preferred physician or clinic according to the
preliminary diagnosis and application, if necessary, with artificial intelligence technology, as
well as to ensure security in all its buildings and facilities, units and branches. It stores personal
data and processes it when necessary, in accordance with the provisions of the Law and other
legislation and the principles contained in the Policy, for the purpose of monitoring entrances
and exits with security cameras.
Our company policy on the use of Artificial Intelligence has been prepared in accordance with
the "Recommendations on the Protection of Personal Data in the Field of Artificial Intelligence"
guide published by Law Numbered 6698. (“KVKK”)
For this purpose, we act in accordance with the following board recommendations in our service
delivery and development processes:
 An approach based on personal data privacy is taken into consideration in the design,
consistent with national and international regulations and/or documents.
 A cautious approach based on appropriate risk prevention and mitigation measures is
adopted, taking into account the possible negative consequences on fundamental rights
and freedoms.
 At every stage of data processing, including data collection, fundamental rights and
freedoms are respected, and the risk of discrimination or other negative effects and
prejudices that may occur on the relevant persons are prevented.
13
 Minimum data usage should be achieved by evaluating the quality, nature, source,
quantity, category and content of the personal data used; The accuracy of the developed
model is constantly monitored.
 Algorithm models taken out of context are carefully evaluated for the risk of causing
negative effects on individuals and society.
 Academic institutions that can contribute to the design of human rights-based, ethical
and socially oriented artificial intelligence applications and the detection of potential
biases should be contacted; Opinions of impartial experts and organizations are sought
in areas where transparency and stakeholder participation may be difficult.
 Individuals are given the right to object to processing based on technologies that affect
their views and personal development.
 Considering the power of artificial intelligence systems to analyze and use personal
data, the rights of the relevant persons arising from national and international legislation
are protected in the processing of personal data.
 Risk assessment based on the active participation of individuals and groups that are
likely to be particularly affected by the practices is encouraged.
 Products and services are designed to ensure that individuals are not exposed to a
decision that will affect them based on automatic processing, without taking into
account their own opinions.
 Alternatives that interfere less with personal rights should be offered in production, and
users' freedom of choice is guaranteed.
 Algorithms are adopted to ensure accountability for all stakeholders in terms of
compliance with personal data protection law, starting from the design of products and
services throughout their life cycle.
 The user's right to stop data processing should be granted and the possibility of deleting,
destroying or anonymizing user data is envisaged.
 Persons interacting with the application should be informed about the reasons for the
personal data processing activity, the details of the methods used in the processing of
personal data and the possible consequences, and an effective data processing approval
mechanism is designed when necessary.
3.7. TRANSFER OF PERSONAL DATA
DentisToday, may transfer Personal Data and/or Personal Data of Special Nature belonging to
the Data Owner that it legally obtained, in accordance with the purpose of processing data, by
taking necessary security precautions, to third persons on a limited basis. In this direction,
14
DentisToday can transfer Personal Data to third persons, in the circumstance where one of the
conditions stated under this Policy or one of the conditions specified below.
 In case the Data Owner grants her/his explicit consent,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data is regulated explicitly under the Laws,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data is mandatory for the protection of life or
physical integrity of the Data Owner or any other persons and the Data Owner
is incapable of giving her/his consent due to the actual impossibility or her/his
consent is not deemed legally valid,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data belonging to the parties of an agreement
is necessary provided that it is directly related to the establishment or execution
of such agreement,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data is mandatory for DentisToday to perform
its legal obligations,
 In case Personal Data is made available to the public by the Data Owner,
her/himself,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data is mandatory for the establishment,
execution or protection of a right,
 In case the transfer of Personal Data is mandatory for the legitimate interest of
DentisToday, provided that this transfer shall not violate the fundamental rights
and freedoms of the Data Owner.
3.8. TRANSFER OF PERSONAL DATA ABROAD
As a rule, DentisToday does not transfer Personal Data abroad. However, it declares that it can
make transfers in the event of the following situations, provided that it takes the necessary
precautions and precautions and complies with the legislation. In line with legitimate and lawful
Personal Data processing purposes, the Data Owner's personal data may be transferred if there
is explicit consent or if the Data Owner does not have explicit consent, if there is an adequacy
decision regarding the country to which the transfer will be made, sectors within the country or
international organizations.
All data collected through DentisToday's mobile application and website are stored in a
domestic cloud system, and there is no international data transfer in this data.
4. PRINCIPLES REGARDING THE RETENTION PERIODS OF PERSONAL
DATA
Personal data is retained by DentisToday, for the period of time specified under the related
legislation and in accordance with its legal obligations. The retention periods are shown under
the Data Controller Registry Information (Verbis) system, publicly.
15
In case the period of time for the retention of personal data has not been regulated under the
related legislation, in connection with the activity that DentisToday conducted while processing
such data, the personal data is processed by DentisToday for a period of time that requires it to
be processed in line with the practices of DentisToday and commercial practices and then it is
erased, destructed or anonymized. Personal data of which processing purpose is disappeared
and personal data that is required to be erased/anonymized by its data owners and if the retention
period of time determined by the related legislation and DentisToday has lapsed, it is retained
only to constitute evidence in the potential legal disputes or to claim the relevant right related
to personal data or to establish a defence. DentisToday, while determining the retention period
of time of personal data, base on the statute of limitations specified under the related legislation.
Personal data retained for such purpose can be accessed only by limited persons only when it
is required to be used in a legal dispute and such data cannot be used for purposes other than
this. At the end of such period of time, personal data is erased, destructed or anonymized.
5. DELETION, DESTRUCTION AND ANONYMIZATION OF PERSONAL DATA
Although Personal Data has been processed in accordance with the provisions of the relevant
law as regulated in Article 7 of the Law and Article 138 of the Turkish Penal Code, it is deleted
by DentisToday ex officio or upon the request of the personal data owner, if the reasons
requiring processing are eliminated. , is destroyed or made anonymous.
Article 7 of KVKK also regulates the deletion, destruction and anonymization of personal data.
Accordingly, even though personal data has been processed in accordance with the law, if the
reasons requiring processing are eliminated, these data may be processed ex officio or in the
relevant
It is deleted, destroyed or made anonymous by our company upon the request of the person.

5. OBLIGATIONS AND RIGHTS
5.1. CLARIFICATION AND PROVIDING INFORMATION OBLIGATION OF
DENTISTODAY
In accordance with Article 10 of the Law, DentisToday clarifies Data Owners during the
acquisition of personal data. Within this context, DentisToday provides information to the Data
Owner on;
 The identity of the Data Controller and its representative, if any,
 For purpose of processing Personal Data,
 To whom and for what purposes the processed Personal Data shall be
transferred,
 The method and legal ground of processing Personal Data and
 Rights of the Data Owner.
It is stated under Article 20 of the Constitution that everybody has the right to be informed on
their personal data. Accordingly, the right “to request information” is stated among the rights
of personal data owners under Article 11 of the Law. In this direction, DentisToday provides
information to the Data Owner upon her/his request of information pursuant to Article 20 of the
Constitution and Article 11 of the Law. You may reach further information with regard to this
subject from the Rights of the Data Owner in the Policy and the Clarification Text.
5.2. RIGHTS OF PERSONAL DATA OWNER
Personal Data Owners have the following rights:
 To learn as to whether personal data of Data Owner is processed or not by
DentisToday,
 To request information on personal processing activity, if such Personal Data
is processed before DentisToday,
17
 To lease the purpose of her/his personal data processing and whether such data
is used for the intended purpose, if such Personal Data is processed before
DentisToday,
 To request information on third parties to whom Personal Data is transferred at
home or abroad,
 To request rectification of the incomplete and inaccurate Personal Data, if any,
 To request the notification for the incomplete and inaccurate Personal Data
processed before DentisToday to third persons to whom such Personal Data is
transferred,
 To request the erasure or destruction or anonymization of Personal Data in case
the reasons of processing such Personal Data are disappeared although such
Personal Data is processed in accordance with the provisions of the Law and
other related laws,
 To request the notification of such circumstance where the persons of
processing Personal Data is disappeared to third persons to whom Personal
Data has been transferred,
 To object to the analysing results that are against the Personal Data Owner
whose Personal Data processed by DentisToday has been analysed exclusively
by automatic means,
 To request compensation for the damages arising out of the illegal processing
of Personal Data,
Data Owners can send their requests concerning the execution of the Law, in writing, via
the “Application Form related to the Application to be Made by the Person Concerned (Data
Owner) to the Data Controller as per the Protection of Personal Data Law numbered 6698”
and other methods determined by the Board to DentisToday. Please click here for the Form.
5.3. EXCEPTIONS
Since the following circumstances are excluded from the scope of the Law as per Articles 28
of the KVKK, data owners cannot claim their aforementioned rights:
 Personal data is processed by real persons within the scope of purely personal
activities of the data owner or of family members living together with her/him
in the same residence provided that it is not to be disclosed to third parties and
the obligations on data security are to be complied with.
 Personal data is processed for the purposes of official statistics and for research,
planning and statistical purposes after having been anonymized.
 Personal data is processed with artistic, historical, literary or scientific
purposes, or within the scope of freedom of expression, provided that national
defence, national security, public security, public order, economic security,
right to privacy or personal rights are not violated or personal data is processed
so as not to constitute a crime.
18
 Personal data is processed within the scope of preventive, protective and
intelligence activities carried out by public institutions and organizations duly
authorized and assigned to ensure national defence, national security, public
security, public order or economic security.
 Personal data is processed by judicial authorities or enforcement authorities
with regard to the investigation, prosecution, criminal proceedings or
enforcement proceedings.
Clarification Text of DentisToday shall not be applied as per Article 28/2 of the KVKK. under
the following circumstances:
 Personal data processing is required for the prevention of a crime or criminal
investigation.
 Personal data processing is carried out on the data which is made public by the
data owner her/himself.
 Personal data processing is required for inspection or regulatory duties and
disciplinary investigation or prosecution to be carried out by the public
institutions and organizations and by professional associations having the
status of a public institution, assigned and authorised for such actions, in
accordance with the authority granted to the same by the law.
 Personal data processing is required for the protection of the State’s economic
and financial interests with regard to budget, tax-related and financial issues.
6. CATEGORIZATION OF PERSONAL DATA
Personal data in the following categories are processed before DentisToday, for the legitimate
and legal personal data processing purposes, based on and limited to one or more than one
conditions of personal data processing conditions stated under Article 5 of the KVKK, by being
in compliance with the general principles stated under the KVKK, particularly principles
specified under Article 5 related to the processing personal data and all obligations regulated
under the KVKK and by being limited to the subjects (Customers, Users, Patients and Patient
candidates, Visitors, Employee Candidates, Company Representatives, Suppliers, Business
Partners, etc.) within the scope of the Policy, by providing information to the person's concerns
as per Article 10 of the KVKK.

EXPLANATION
Identity Information
Data that is explicitly belonging to an identified or identifiable
real person; processed fully or partially through automatic means
or provided that the process is a part of any data registry system,
through non-automatic means; that contains information on the
identity of the person; documents such as driving license, identity
card and passports that include information such as name-
surname, T.R. identity number, nationality information, mother’s
name- father’s name, place of birth, date of birth, gender and
information such as tax number, SGK number, signature
information, vehicle plate, etc.
Contact Information
Data that is explicitly belonging to an identified or identifiable
real person; processed fully or partially through automatic means
or provided that the process is a part of any data registry system,
through non-automatic means; information such as telephone
number, address, e-mail address, fax number, IP address.
Location Data
Data that is explicitly belonging to an identified or identifiable
real person; processed fully or partially through automatic means
or provided that the process is a part of any data registry system,
through non-automatic means; that determines the location data
of the personal data owner during the usage of products and
services of DentisToday within the operations conducted by the
business units of DentisToday or the location of the employees
of entities that our Company is incorporation with while they are
driving the vehicles of DentisToday; GPS location, travel data,
etc.
Information on Family
Members and Relatives
Data that is explicitly belonging to an identified or identifiable
real person; processed fully or partially through automatic means
or provided that the process is a part of any data registry system,
through non-automatic means; regarding the products and
services offered by DentisToday within the operations conducted
by the business units of DentisToday or regarding the family
members (for instance, spouse, mother, father, children),
relatives of the personal data owner and other persons that can be
contacted for emergency for the purpose of protecting legal and
other interests of DentisToday and personal data owner.
